caption.title: Transmission rate and CHIKV virus titer in saliva at 7 and 14 dpi in AR wP, S ANG wild-type and Wolbachia-cured Ae. albopictus.
caption.p: wPip = AR wP Ae. albopictus; wAlbA & wAlbB = S ANG wild-type Ae. albopictus; w- = Wolbachia-cured S ANG; dpi = days post infection. Mosquitoes were infected with CHIKV at a titer of 10 7 FFU(PFU)/mL. (A) Transmission rate was not significantly different between Ae. albopictus lines both at 7 and 14 dpi (Fisher exact test, P < 0.05). (B) Virus titer in female Ae. albopictus did not differ between lines at both 7 and 14 dpi (Kruskalâ€“Wallis test: P < 0.05).
